[SN]TITLE[SN]
Arthur Green death in Prestwick: Three face murder charge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three men have appeared in court charged with the murder of a 60-year-old man in Ayrshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Harry Hood, 44, Dale Russell, 34, and Ross Russell, 33, are accused of killing Arthur Green, whose body was discovered by a relative at his home in Prestwick on 20 November.
They made no plea or declaration during a private hearing at Ayr Sheriff Court.
They were granted bail but this was appealed immediately by prosecutors and all three were remanded in custody.
A further hearing is due to take place within 48 hours.
